               <persName id="t17500530-7-person81">
                  John 
                  Leaver 
               <interp inst="t17500530-7-person81" type="surname" value="Leaver"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17500530-7-person81" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17500530-7-person81" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , he has got a handkerchief in his hand, which he was going to drop. He had not ran above eight or ten yards before he was taken. I took the handkerchief out of his hand, and found it to be my own. The excuse he made, was, he took it up.</p>
               <p>Q. When had you your handkerchief last, before you lost it?</p>
               <p>Price. I had it when I was at Holbourn-bridge, in my left side pocket, and this was before we came to the four lamps.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. As I was coming home, I saw a mob, I cross'd over the way, this man came over the way and said, I have lost my handkerchief. He could not find any thing about me, the handkerchief was lying by a post.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. I took it out of his hand.</p>
